}}{{!

Included on Cython structs in properties for retrieving child values from
that struct. Most types can be returned directly and converted to python objects
by Cython. Complex objects need to be wrapped or decoded appropriately. Structs
are special because we try to memoize their wrappers on the parent handler
if they have been previously retrieved.

}}{{!
For the Thrift field foo, this generates the C++ accessor expression to obtain
the field value: plain name if no ref accessor, or the appropriate
_ref().value() / _ref().value_unchecked() variant.
}}
{{#let partial cython_field_value_ref |field|}}
{{#pragma ignore-newlines}}
  {{#if (not field.has_ref_accessor?)}}
{{field.py_name}}
  {{#else if (and field.optional? (not field.boxed_ref?))}}
{{field.py_name}}_ref().value_unchecked()
  {{#else}}
{{field.py_name}}_ref().value()
  {{/if (not field.has_ref_accessor?)}}
{{/let partial}}
{{!
